Prerequistes: the NOS in the primary region is using ebs-sc.

Steps
- On devtest03, take a snapshot (s0) of NOS by PSM.
- Wait until the s0 is available. e.g.:
    âœ— kubectl get volumesnapshot tldbtestpsm-1633444131780
    NAME                        READYTOUSE   SOURCEPVC                   SOURCESNAPSHOTCONTENT   RESTORESIZE   SNAPSHOTCLASS   SNAPSHOTCONTENT                                    CREATIONTIME   AGE
    tldbtestpsm-1633444131780   true         tldbtestpsm-tldbtestpsm-0                           10Gi          csi-snapclass   snapcontent-61ed4d06-8244-4315-a40e-a41d1f9d3fed   114d           114d
- Go to AWS console, find the ebs snapshot of s0. Get the id and region.
- Follow https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/ec2/copy-snapshot.html to copy the snapshot to devtestfkt03.
    - Run the command in the seondary region.
    - Q: can I use default kms-key-id???
    - e.g.
        aws ec2 copy-snapshot \
            --source-region us-west-2 \
            --source-snapshot-id snap-066877671789bd71b \
            --encrypted \
            --kms-key-id alias/my-kms-key
    - Get the output, which is the snapshot (s1) id in fkt.
- Use s1 to restore a PVC.